HEADWORD: Ipomœic
<hw>Ip`o*m⟦oe⟧"ic</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧p`⟦osl⟧*m⟦emac⟧"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an
acid obtained by the oxidation of convolvulin (obtained from jalap, the
tubers of <spn>Ipom⟦oe⟧a purga</spn>), and identical in most of its
properties with sebacic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ipsus</ent>⟦br⟧
